  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to analyse the usability of ultrasonography together with
      biomarkers in the investigation of patients diagnosed with juvenile idiopathic arthritis. The
      investigators hypothesize that serum and urine markers of cartilage and bone synthesis and
      degradation, together with ultrasound measurements of joint cartilage thickness, are useful
      tools in the early evaluation of JIA patients, - as diagnostic, prognostic and monitoring
      methods.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
